// In this continuation of the read example, the text property is allowed to be modified outside of the
//  read function because its parent object isn’t explicitly described as a Text until inside the function.
//  pageIsh is allowed to be used as a Page because a writable property is assignable
//  to a readonly property (mutable properties can be read from, which is all a readonly property needs):

